<subSubSection id="C35B6568376C3F0FFF1DF8DB96D53741" pageId="10" pageNumber="119" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BFE36E3376C3F0FFF1DF8DB91A436E1" blockId="10.[136,776,1879,2095]" lastBlockId="10.[834,1476,189,661]" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1376C3F0FFF1DF8DB9372331B" bold="true" box="[136,260,1879,1903]" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male: fore femur variably incrassate (ratio length/width: 3.03–4.36), ventral surface of fore femur in distal one-fourth with black indentation which proximally marked by distinct tooth, and with single stout sub-apical tooth; inner surface of fore tibia subbasally with tooth-like elevation (indistinct in males with small fore leg) (
<figureCitation id="137A2A66376C3F0FFD3EF87B92D13C5B" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="9.[113,157,1339,1361]" captionTargetBox="[114,1452,190,1328]" captionTargetId="figure-9@9.[108,1471,181,1335]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs. 44–55. Morphological features of Metrocoris species. 44–46: M. stranguloides. 44, 45: right fore legs of male. 46: sternum 7 of female, ventral view. 47–51: M. bilobatoides. 47, 48: right fore leg of male, same scale. 49, 50: tergum 7 of female, dorsal view (49: specimen from Tam Dao; 50: specimen from Lao Cai). 51: sternum 7 of female, ventral view. 52–55: M. vietnamensis (52–55 reproduced and modified from Tran &amp; Zettel, 2005). 52, 53: right fore legs of male. 54: left paramere. 55: sternum 7 of female, in situ (44, 45, 47, 48, 52, 53 same scale; 46, 49–51, 55 same scale)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4502646" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4502646/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Figs. 52, 53</figureCitation>
). Male genitalia: pygophore not raised posteriorly, caudal margin broadly rounded, caudal face with paired, shallow impressions, dorso-lateral process curved and apically blunt (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B12376C3F0FFCE0FF72963A3561" author="Tran AD &amp; Zettel H" box="[885,1100,253,277]" pageId="10" pageNumber="119" pagination="41 - 54" refId="ref42062" refString="Tran AD &amp; Zettel H (2005) Two new species of the water strider genus Metrocoris Mayr, 1865 (Insecta: Heteroptera: Gerridae) from Vietnam, and redescription of M. femoratus (Paiva, 1919) from Meghalaya, India. Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wein, Serie B, 106: 41 - 54." type="journal article" year="2005">Tran &amp; Zettel, 2005</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation id="137A2A66376C3F0FFBC2FF7196CD3561" box="[1111,1211,253,277]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[135,179,1891,1913]" captionTargetBox="[264,1325,243,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-8@4.[152,1455,189,1875]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 3–17. Dorsal colour patterns of Metrocoris species, all apterous morph. 3, 4: M. stranguloides, specimens from Vietnam, Gia Lai Prov., 60 km N. of An Khe (CL 4309). 5, 6: M. bilobatoides, specimens from Vietnam, Lao Cai Prov., 12 km NW. of Sa Pa (CL 4404). 7, 8: M. johnpolhemi, new species, specimens from Vietnam, Lai Chau Prov.; male from 12 km N. of Lai Chau (CL 4410), female from Nam Ceung stream (CL 4409). 9: M. vietnamensis, paratype, from Vietnam, Da Nang Prov., Ba Na - Nui Chua (TAD0334) (9 reproduced and modified from Tran &amp; Zettel, 2005). 10, 11: M. quynhi, specimens from Vietnam, Lao Cai Prov., 18 km NW. of Sa Pa (CL 4400). 12, 13: M. obscurus, specimens from Vietnam, Lao Cai Prov., 4 km NE. of Sa Pa (CL 4407). 14, 15: M. acutus, specimens from Vietnam, Hai Hung Prov., 22 km N. of Chi Linh (CL 4375). 16, 17: M. nigrofascioides, specimens from Vietnam, Binh Dinh Prov., An Khe Pass (CL 4291)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4502640" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4502640/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Figs. 4, 5</figureCitation>
); proctiger elongate (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B12376C3F0FFCD6FE92966F3541" author="Tran AD &amp; Zettel H" box="[835,1049,285,309]" pageId="10" pageNumber="119" pagination="41 - 54" refId="ref42062" refString="Tran AD &amp; Zettel H (2005) Two new species of the water strider genus Metrocoris Mayr, 1865 (Insecta: Heteroptera: Gerridae) from Vietnam, and redescription of M. femoratus (Paiva, 1919) from Meghalaya, India. Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wein, Serie B, 106: 41 - 54." type="journal article" year="2005">Tran &amp; Zettel, 2005</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation id="137A2A66376C3F0FFBB7FE9196173541" box="[1058,1121,285,309]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[135,179,1891,1913]" captionTargetBox="[264,1325,243,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-8@4.[152,1455,189,1875]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 3–17. Dorsal colour patterns of Metrocoris species, all apterous morph. 3, 4: M. stranguloides, specimens from Vietnam, Gia Lai Prov., 60 km N. of An Khe (CL 4309). 5, 6: M. bilobatoides, specimens from Vietnam, Lao Cai Prov., 12 km NW. of Sa Pa (CL 4404). 7, 8: M. johnpolhemi, new species, specimens from Vietnam, Lai Chau Prov.; male from 12 km N. of Lai Chau (CL 4410), female from Nam Ceung stream (CL 4409). 9: M. vietnamensis, paratype, from Vietnam, Da Nang Prov., Ba Na - Nui Chua (TAD0334) (9 reproduced and modified from Tran &amp; Zettel, 2005). 10, 11: M. quynhi, specimens from Vietnam, Lao Cai Prov., 18 km NW. of Sa Pa (CL 4400). 12, 13: M. obscurus, specimens from Vietnam, Lao Cai Prov., 4 km NE. of Sa Pa (CL 4407). 14, 15: M. acutus, specimens from Vietnam, Hai Hung Prov., 22 km N. of Chi Linh (CL 4375). 16, 17: M. nigrofascioides, specimens from Vietnam, Binh Dinh Prov., An Khe Pass (CL 4291)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4502640" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4502640/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); paramere prominent, falciform, strongly curved and apically strongly narrowed (
<figureCitation id="137A2A66376C3F0FFAF5FEB197C23521" box="[1376,1460,317,341]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="9.[113,157,1339,1361]" captionTargetBox="[114,1452,190,1328]" captionTargetId="figure-9@9.[108,1471,181,1335]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs. 44–55. Morphological features of Metrocoris species. 44–46: M. stranguloides. 44, 45: right fore legs of male. 46: sternum 7 of female, ventral view. 47–51: M. bilobatoides. 47, 48: right fore leg of male, same scale. 49, 50: tergum 7 of female, dorsal view (49: specimen from Tam Dao; 50: specimen from Lao Cai). 51: sternum 7 of female, ventral view. 52–55: M. vietnamensis (52–55 reproduced and modified from Tran &amp; Zettel, 2005). 52, 53: right fore legs of male. 54: left paramere. 55: sternum 7 of female, in situ (44, 45, 47, 48, 52, 53 same scale; 46, 49–51, 55 same scale)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4502646" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4502646/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Fig. 54</figureCitation>
); endosoma: dorsal sclerite long and recurved proximally, apical accessory sclerite distinct, lateral sclerite very large, slightly curved, ventral sclerite short, thin accessory lateral sclerite present (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B12376C3F0FFB8DFE32969A35A1" author="Tran AD &amp; Zettel H" box="[1048,1260,445,469]" pageId="10" pageNumber="119" pagination="41 - 54" refId="ref42062" refString="Tran AD &amp; Zettel H (2005) Two new species of the water strider genus Metrocoris Mayr, 1865 (Insecta: Heteroptera: Gerridae) from Vietnam, and redescription of M. femoratus (Paiva, 1919) from Meghalaya, India. Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wein, Serie B, 106: 41 - 54." type="journal article" year="2005">Tran &amp; Zettel, 2005</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation id="137A2A66376C3F0FFB60FE31972135A1" box="[1269,1367,445,469]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[135,179,1891,1913]" captionTargetBox="[264,1325,243,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-8@4.[152,1455,189,1875]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 3–17. Dorsal colour patterns of Metrocoris species, all apterous morph. 3, 4: M. stranguloides, specimens from Vietnam, Gia Lai Prov., 60 km N. of An Khe (CL 4309). 5, 6: M. bilobatoides, specimens from Vietnam, Lao Cai Prov., 12 km NW. of Sa Pa (CL 4404). 7, 8: M. johnpolhemi, new species, specimens from Vietnam, Lai Chau Prov.; male from 12 km N. of Lai Chau (CL 4410), female from Nam Ceung stream (CL 4409). 9: M. vietnamensis, paratype, from Vietnam, Da Nang Prov., Ba Na - Nui Chua (TAD0334) (9 reproduced and modified from Tran &amp; Zettel, 2005). 10, 11: M. quynhi, specimens from Vietnam, Lao Cai Prov., 18 km NW. of Sa Pa (CL 4400). 12, 13: M. obscurus, specimens from Vietnam, Lao Cai Prov., 4 km NE. of Sa Pa (CL 4407). 14, 15: M. acutus, specimens from Vietnam, Hai Hung Prov., 22 km N. of Chi Linh (CL 4375). 16, 17: M. nigrofascioides, specimens from Vietnam, Binh Dinh Prov., An Khe Pass (CL 4291)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4502640" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4502640/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Figs. 7, 8</figureCitation>
). Sternum 7 of female (
<figureCitation id="137A2A66376C3F0FFC45FE5196553581" box="[976,1059,477,501]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="9.[113,157,1339,1361]" captionTargetBox="[114,1452,190,1328]" captionTargetId="figure-9@9.[108,1471,181,1335]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs. 44–55. Morphological features of Metrocoris species. 44–46: M. stranguloides. 44, 45: right fore legs of male. 46: sternum 7 of female, ventral view. 47–51: M. bilobatoides. 47, 48: right fore leg of male, same scale. 49, 50: tergum 7 of female, dorsal view (49: specimen from Tam Dao; 50: specimen from Lao Cai). 51: sternum 7 of female, ventral view. 52–55: M. vietnamensis (52–55 reproduced and modified from Tran &amp; Zettel, 2005). 52, 53: right fore legs of male. 54: left paramere. 55: sternum 7 of female, in situ (44, 45, 47, 48, 52, 53 same scale; 46, 49–51, 55 same scale)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4502646" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4502646/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Fig. 55</figureCitation>
): large, slightly longer than preceding abdominal sterna together, posterior one-third constricted, bifid forming two widely separated lobes, slightly slanting but not curved dorsad; notch between lobes as wide as each lobe; apices of lobes pointed, reaching apex of abdomen in ventral view.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFE36E3376C3F0FFCD6FD3196D53741" blockId="10.[835,1475,701,821]" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">
Size: apterous males: length 6.0–6.8 (
<typeStatus id="54FA8841376C3F0FFB77FD31973736A1" box="[1250,1345,701,725]" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">holotype</typeStatus>
6.7), width 2.67–3.06 (
<typeStatus id="54FA8841376C3F0FFC28FD51966A3681" box="[957,1052,733,757]" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">holotype</typeStatus>
2.96), macropterous males: length 6.2, width 2.73; apterous females: length 5.1–5.5 (
<typeStatus id="54FA8841376C3F0FFAA6FD7197FD3761" box="[1331,1419,765,789]" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">allotype</typeStatus>
5.4), width 2.81–3.10 (
<typeStatus id="54FA8841376C3F0FFB91FC91962A3741" box="[1028,1116,797,821]" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">allotype</typeStatus>
3.01).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35B6568376C3F0FFCD6FCD197C53001" pageId="10" pageNumber="119" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFE36E3376C3F0FFCD6FCD197C53001" blockId="10.[834,1476,861,1141]" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1376C3F0FFCD6FCD191C63701" bold="true" box="[835,944,861,885]" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60376C3F0FFC20FCD296C33701" authorityName="Tran &amp; Zettel" authorityYear="2005" box="[949,1205,862,885]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vietnamensis">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1376C3F0FFC20FCD296C33701" box="[949,1205,862,885]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Metrocoris vietnamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60376C3F0FFAD9FCD291D037E1" authorityName="den Boer" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bilobatus">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1376C3F0FFAD9FCD291D037E1" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Metrocoris bilobatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group (sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B12376C3F0FFB1BFCF1970437E1" author="Chen PP &amp; Nieser N" box="[1166,1394,893,917]" pageId="10" pageNumber="119" pagination="45 - 82" refId="ref41516" refString="Chen PP &amp; Nieser N (1993) A taxonomic revision of the Oriental water strider genus Metrocoris Mayr (Hemiptera, Gerridae). Part I and Part II. Steenstrupia, 19 (1 - 2): 1 - 43, 45 - 82." type="journal article" year="1993">Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993</bibRefCitation>
), and is the second species of this group found in 
<collectingCountry id="F3567673376C3F0FFA90FC11971237C1" box="[1285,1380,925,949]" name="Vietnam" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, the first being 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60376C3F0FFC11FC32965D37A1" authorityName="Chen &amp; Nieser" authorityYear="1993" box="[900,1067,957,981]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bilobatoides">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1376C3F0FFC11FC32965D37A1" box="[900,1067,957,981]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">M. bilobatoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B12376C3F0FFBCAFC31973437A1" author="Chen PP &amp; Nieser N" box="[1119,1346,957,981]" pageId="10" pageNumber="119" pagination="45 - 82" refId="ref41516" refString="Chen PP &amp; Nieser N (1993) A taxonomic revision of the Oriental water strider genus Metrocoris Mayr (Hemiptera, Gerridae). Part I and Part II. Steenstrupia, 19 (1 - 2): 1 - 43, 45 - 82." type="journal article" year="1993">Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993</bibRefCitation>
). A detailed comparison of 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60376C3F0FFC4BFC5296953781" authorityName="Tran &amp; Zettel" authorityYear="2005" box="[990,1251,990,1013]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vietnamensis">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1376C3F0FFC4BFC5296953781" box="[990,1251,990,1013]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Metrocoris vietnamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with its congeners in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60376C3F0FFCF8FC7291833061" authorityName="den Boer" authorityYear="1965" box="[877,1013,1021,1045]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bilobatus">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1376C3F0FFCF8FC7291833061" box="[877,1013,1021,1045]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">M. bilobatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group has already been provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B12376C3F0FFA07FC7296353041" author="Tran AD &amp; Zettel H" pageId="10" pageNumber="119" pagination="41 - 54" refId="ref42062" refString="Tran AD &amp; Zettel H (2005) Two new species of the water strider genus Metrocoris Mayr, 1865 (Insecta: Heteroptera: Gerridae) from Vietnam, and redescription of M. femoratus (Paiva, 1919) from Meghalaya, India. Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wein, Serie B, 106: 41 - 54." type="journal article" year="2005">Tran &amp; Zettel (2005: 44–45)</bibRefCitation>
. For further comparisons with other members of 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60376C3F0FFC50FBB2963D3021" authorityName="den Boer" authorityYear="1965" box="[965,1099,1085,1109]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bilobatus">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1376C3F0FFC50FBB2963D3021" box="[965,1099,1085,1109]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">M. bilobatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group which occur in 
<collectingCountry id="F3567673376C3F0FFAADFBB197E13021" box="[1336,1431,1085,1109]" name="Vietnam" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, see subsequent Remarks under 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60376C3F0FFBE4FBD2976C3001" authority="A.D. &amp; Polhemus, 2017" authorityName="A.D. &amp; Polhemus" authorityYear="2017" box="[1137,1306,1117,1141]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="johnpolhemi" status="new species">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1376C3F0FFBE4FBD2976C3001" box="[1137,1306,1117,1141]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">M. johnpolhemi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A206578A376C3F0FFABCFBD297D93001" box="[1321,1455,1117,1141]" pageId="10" pageNumber="119" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
